Running grabsy.sh alone will trigger the system to prompt for an existing directory

freedom:~ erichagstrom$ /Users/erichagstrom/grabsy.sh
Enter destination directory for native OSX screenshots: ~/Pictures/Screenshots
Changing screenshot destination directory to ~/Pictures/Screenshots
freedom:~ erichagstrom$ 

Adding default to the grabsy.sh command will reset the directory to system defaults

freedom:~ erichagstrom$ /Users/erichagstrom/Downloads/grabsy-master/grabsy.sh default
Changing screenshot destination directory to /Users/erichagstrom/Desktop

Any screenshots you take using CMD+SHIFT+4 or CMD+SHIFT+3 will save to the new location or the default location
depending on the option you choose. 
